text: Grant County is a county located in the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 28,185. Its county seat is Silver City. The county was founded in 1868 and named for Ulysses S. Grant, 18th President of the United States. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:1860s establishments in New Mexico Territory Category:1868 establishments in the United States
title: Grant County, New Mexico
